MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1762303661}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 5f7201a12d95ffc409449d95f23cf332, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 10, y: 10, z: 10, w: 10}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_FontData:
    m_Font: {fileID: 10102, guid: 0000000000000000e000000000000000, type: 0}
    m_FontSize: 12
    m_FontStyle: 0
    m_BestFit: 0
    m_MinSize: 10
    m_MaxSize: 40
    m_Alignment: 3
    m_AlignByGeometry: 0
    m_RichText: 1
    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: "\n<b>How to Play</b>\r\n\r\n\u2022 Rotate view: Right-click (or swipe)
    to twirl the camera around your ball ~ don\u2019t be shy, explore those angles! 
    \r\n\u2022 Shoot: Left-click and drag backwards (aim + power). Release to send
    your Golfense flying!  \r\n\u2022 Change your mind? Drag back onto the ball and
    release. Instant undo ~ like magic for indecisive players.  \r\n\u2022 Watch
    the prediction: A helpful line/power bar shows your bold plan (or impending chaos). 
    \r\n\u2022 Check scores: Pause anytime or wait for the end-of-hole panel to see
    who\u2019s really defending their place.\r\n\r\n\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\r\n\r\n<b>Game
    Flow</b>\r\n\r\n\u2022 Both players must get their balls in the hole within 13
    shots. If not, the round \u201Cresets\u201D ~ defend your Golfense!  \r\n\u2022
    Each hole: Fewer shots = win; but the final Golfense champion is the one with
    the lowest total after 9 holes.  \r\n\u2022 After each hole, loser gets first
    pick in the strategic phase:  \r\n    <b>Option 1:</b> Roll speed multiplier
    ~ affect yourself, the opponent, or choose \u201Cno change\u201D if you want
    to play safe (or just lazy).  \r\n    <b>Option 2:</b> Random map expansion at
    the start of the course.  \r\n    <b>Option 3:</b> Random map expansion at the
    end. For those who love cliffhangers.  \r\n\u2022 Balls love the ground and walls
    ~ sticky physics mean wild slopes are possible, but don\u2019t launch yourself
    off the map unless you want to show off!  \r\n\u2022 Use collisions: bump, block,
    or gently nudge your rival ~ be clever, be cheeky, be Golfense!  \r\n\u2022 Sticky
    walls, sneaky corners, and bonus backspin are all in play.  \r\n\u2022 <i>\u201CGolfense
    feature\u201D:</i> If your ball nearly stops and then rolls back down a hill,
    you get an extra turn. Defend your turn like a pro! \U0001F609  \r\n\u2022 <i>\u201CUntamed
    bug\u201D:</i> Gaps between map tiles sometimes zap balls in odd ways. No potion
    fix yet, but the legend lives on! \U0001F9EA\r\n\r\n\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\r\n\r\n<b>Summary:</b> 
    \r\nHave fun, be clever, and always defend your Golfense winning placement! There\u2019s
    only one way to the top ~ outplay, outlast, and out-Golfense.\r\n"
